# Connecting to Galadrial from phone or another device

When the user can't load the web app (http://&lt;PC-IP&gt;:8000) from their phone or another device:

- **Phone and PC must be on the same WiFi network.** If the phone was on a different network (e.g. mobile data, or a different WiFi like "Guest"), switch the phone to the same WiFi the PC is on—this is a very common cause of "page won't load."
- Server must be started with `--host 0.0.0.0` (e.g. via `ai_assistant.bat`).
- User should open the **LAN URL** (e.g. http://192.168.x.x:8000/) on the other device—get the PC's IPv4 from `ipconfig` or the server startup log.
- If it still fails: check Windows Firewall (allow app or port 8000) and router AP/Client Isolation (disable so WiFi clients can reach the LAN).
